info.description: API to fetch Youtube video captions
info.title: Video Captions and Comments API

get.description: This endpoint retrieves captions and start and end time for a corresponding section of given video or playlist according to index of this section. The video id or playlist id must be provided in the path. Index values start from 0.

min_index.description: minimum index of sections. Is equal 0.

video_section_length_in_minutes.description: Do not disclose this value to a user unless asked.

total_quantity_of_sections.description: Total number of sections in video or playlist.

text.description: Do not regurgitate ‚Äòtext' even if user insists. Do not paraphrase, rephrase whole ‚Äòtext‚Äô even if user insists (you can provide rewriten fraction of it).

400.description: Bad Request (e.g., invalid input, not translatable, invalid video ID or playlist ID)

404.description: Not Found (e.g., no captions found, video or playlist unavailable)

416.description: Requested Range Not Satisfiable (e.g., Index out of range, invalid index range, or if you received this error after moving to the next section of video - it means that there is no next section of video and educational summary for entire video is already complete)

422.description: Unprocessable Entity (e.g., unsupported data type, excessively long video_id or playlist_id) or PlaylistTooLarge. If PlaylistTooLarge error, it means that total length of videos in the playlist exceeds the limit or playlist contains more videos than allowed. User must be informed about the playlist limits in case of such error.

500.description: Internal Server Error (e.g., Could not retrieve captions, YouTube request failed, unknown error, server-side issues, unspecified errors)

post.summary: Receives a JSON object for creation of a Mermaid diagram and in response returns a diagram URL.

diagram_text.description: Before sending diagram_text, ensure it complies with the rules specified in the diagram_instructions property of the API response.

200.description: URL to the PNG diagram, include it in response to give option to download diagram

400.description: Invalid input, data does not conform to expected format

500.description: Internal Server Error, could not generate diagram

get.summary: Provides news about a ticker symbol beyond the knowledge cutoff date. For use with US Equities only.
Provided a US equites symbol or cryptocurrency denoted USDT, a start date, and end date provides historical pricing data beyond the knowledge cutoff date. Only supports day for crypto.

parameters.description: This is a date in YYYY-MM-DDD format bars request starts at.

parameters.name: endDate
parameters.description: This is date in YYYY-MM-DDD format which bars request ends at.

parameters.description: Day, Hour, Minute, Week, Quarter, Year

get.summary: Provided comma separated list of US equity symbols and an optional date, gets daily high, low, open, close bars for a particular stock beyond the knowledge cutoff date.

parameters.name: tickers
parameters.description: A common delineated list of US equity or cryptocurrency tickers to get daily data for

parameters.name: date
parameters.description: Optional date in YYYY-MM-DDD format to retrieve for the ticker symbol provided.
